    "## Part 1: Understanding Spatial Sampling\n",
    "\n",
    "### 1.1 What is Spatial Sampling?\n",
    "\n",
    "Spatial sampling involves extracting raster values at specific geographic locations. This bridges the gap between:\n",
    "- **Continuous raster data** (elevation, temperature, vegetation indices)\n",
    "- **Point-based observations** (weather stations, sample sites, GPS locations)\n",
    "\n",
    "### 1.2 Coordinate System Considerations\n",
    "\n",
    "Critical aspects of spatial sampling:\n",
    "1. **Coordinate Reference Systems (CRS):** Points and rasters must be in compatible projections\n",
    "2. **Pixel Registration:** Understanding how pixel values relate to geographic coordinates\n",
    "3. **Interpolation Methods:** How to estimate values between pixel centers\n",
    "4. **Edge Effects:** Handling points near or outside raster boundaries"
   ]
  },
