    "## Part 3: Advanced Sampling Techniques\n",
    "\n",
    "### 3.1 Buffered Sampling\n",
    "\n",
    "Instead of sampling at exact point locations, we can:\n",
    "1. Create circular buffers around points\n",
    "2. Extract all pixel values within each buffer\n",
    "3. Calculate statistics (mean, median, std, percentiles)\n",
    "\n",
    "This approach is useful for:\n",
    "- Reducing noise in the data\n",
    "- Representing spatial uncertainty in point locations\n",
    "- Matching the scale of field measurements\n",
    "\n",
    "### 3.2 Multi-band Sampling\n",
    "\n",
    "Extract values from multiple raster bands simultaneously:\n",
    "- Elevation, temperature, and vegetation indices\n",
    "- All spectral bands from satellite imagery\n",
    "- Time series data from different dates"
   ]
